### useNavigation() Hook
```typescript
const nav = useNavigation();
// Returns:
// - nav.push(title, data): Push view onto stack
// - nav.pop(): Pop current view
// - nav.popToRoot(): Clear stack to root
// - nav.currentEntry: Current NavViewData or null (null = root)
// - nav.breadcrumbs: Array<{ label, onBack? }>
// - nav.canGoBack: boolean
// - nav.direction: 'push' | 'pop' | 'none'
